That does not happen by accident.

5549
04:25:52.315 --> 04:25:55.535
It happens because of structure, regulation, accountability,

5550
04:25:55.675 --> 04:25:56.935
and the people who care deeply.

5551
04:25:57.865 --> 04:26:00.285
The welfare standards in Greyhound racing today are not

5552
04:26:00.285 --> 04:26:02.005
with it what they were many years ago.

5553
04:26:02.965 --> 04:26:05.525
I have seen the industry change rapidly and decisively.

5554
04:26:05.935 --> 04:26:07.245
Track standards have improved.

5555
04:26:07.415 --> 04:26:09.245
Veterinary oversight is constant.

5556
04:26:09.885 --> 04:26:11.605
Injuries are reported and investigated.

5557
04:26:11.975 --> 04:26:14.925
Greyhounds track for life, rehoming is no longer optional.

5558
04:26:15.185 --> 04:26:18.325
It is expected and enforced. Greyhound racing.

5559
04:26:18.345 --> 04:26:19.445
New Zealand has built one

5560
04:26:19.445 --> 04:26:21.325
of the strongest welfare frameworks in the world.

5561
04:26:22.215 --> 04:26:25.075
It continues to evolve through ongoing reviews, regulations,

5562
04:26:25.075 --> 04:26:27.915
and investments with a clear focus on improving outcomes

5563
04:26:27.915 --> 04:26:29.995
for greyhounds across every stage of their lives.

5564
04:26:31.135 --> 04:26:33.995
One greyhound I trained named Swimming goat is not just a

5565
04:26:33.995 --> 04:26:35.155
name in a race book to me.

5566
04:26:35.535 --> 04:26:36.555
He is part of our family.

5567
04:26:37.695 --> 04:26:39.355
He won 22 races in a row,

5568
04:26:39.775 --> 04:26:42.275
and every one of those wins came from his love of racing.

5569
04:26:43.055 --> 04:26:44.435
You could feel it when you handled him.

5570
04:26:44.535 --> 04:26:46.955
The excitement, the confidence, the happiness he had, doing

5571
04:26:46.955 --> 04:26:48.035
what he was born to do.

5572
04:26:48.775 --> 04:26:50.515
No one ever had to force him to race.

5573
04:26:50.975 --> 04:26:52.435
Racing was something he wanted.

5574
04:26:52.455 --> 04:26:54.275
Racing, gave him purpose and a joy.

5575
04:26:55.275 --> 04:26:57.615
For many years now, swimming goat has been retired

5576
04:26:57.635 --> 04:26:59.015
and lives inside our home with us.

5577
04:26:59.515 --> 04:27:01.965
He sleeps near the kids, follows us from room to room,

5578
04:27:02.185 --> 04:27:04.125
and has settled into family pet life

5579
04:27:04.125 --> 04:27:05.365
like he has always belonged there.

5580
04:27:06.125 --> 04:27:07.485
Watching him now calm and content,

5581
04:27:07.645 --> 04:27:10.365
I know his life has been fulfilled, not just just

5582
04:27:10.365 --> 04:27:11.845
after racing, but because of it.

5583
04:27:12.305 --> 04:27:14.485
He is living proof that a greyhound can love racing

5584
04:27:14.585 --> 04:27:15.885
and still have a happy, safe,

5585
04:27:15.945 --> 04:27:17.725
deeply loved life after it ends.

5586
04:27:18.865 --> 04:27:20.005
My partner, my parents

5587
04:27:20.025 --> 04:27:22.805
and I have put our life savings into making sure our kennels

5588
04:27:22.805 --> 04:27:24.685
exceed the highest welfare standards in New Zealand.

5589
04:27:25.225 --> 04:27:26.885
We built them with the greyhounds in mind.

5590
04:27:27.025 --> 04:27:29.165
Not for profit, but for their comfort, their routine,

5591
04:27:29.335 --> 04:27:30.765
their enrichment, their safety.

5592
04:27:31.585 --> 04:27:34.285
We do not clock off at five. We do not get weekends.

5593
04:27:34.465 --> 04:27:36.685
We work seven days a week every day of the year

5594
04:27:36.835 --> 04:27:38.725
because of greyhounds rely on us.

5595
04:27:39.585 --> 04:27:41.125
If this proposed bill goes ahead,

5596
04:27:41.145 --> 04:27:42.645
my family will lose two businesses.

5597
04:27:42.705 --> 04:27:45.405
Our racing kennels and our rehoming preparation kennels.

5598
04:27:46.395 --> 04:27:48.275
I have four children who rely on this income

5599
04:27:48.535 --> 04:27:50.515
and on the stability This work provides.

5600
04:27:50.895 --> 04:27:53.315
The economic impact on family like mine is enormous.

5601
04:27:53.935 --> 04:27:56.155
But beyond the financial loss, there is something deeper.

5602
04:27:56.695 --> 04:27:59.115
The mental health impact on this proposed

5603
04:27:59.115 --> 04:28:00.315
bill has already been felt.

5604
04:28:00.815 --> 04:28:03.475
The constant uncertainty, the fear of losing everything.

5605
04:28:03.475 --> 04:28:04.715
We have worked for over decades,

5606
04:28:05.255 --> 04:28:06.515
and the feeling of being judged

5607
04:28:06.535 --> 04:28:08.995
and dismissed despite doing everything asked of us.

5608
04:28:09.425 --> 04:28:11.155
This is taking a real toll on trainers,

5609
04:28:11.155 --> 04:28:12.315
kennel, staff, and families.

5610
04:28:12.975 --> 04:28:15.875
We also employ people for full-time staff

5611
04:28:15.935 --> 04:28:17.315
and two part-time staff.

5612
04:28:17.875 --> 04:28:20.515
A bill of this kind means those people lose their jobs.

5613
04:28:20.935 --> 04:28:22.515
It means more families under stress

5614
04:28:22.535 --> 04:28:23.995
and more livelihoods destroyed.

5615
04:28:24.995 --> 04:28:27.315
Removing a regulated industry does not improve welfare.

5616
04:28:27.535 --> 04:28:28.675
It removes oversight,

5617
04:28:28.675 --> 04:28:31.515
accountability in the very people responsible for caring

5618
04:28:31.515 --> 04:28:33.235
for these greyhounds every single day.

5619
04:28:35.825 --> 04:28:37.725
If the industry is dismantled, the structure

5620
04:28:37.725 --> 04:28:39.525
that ensures greyhounds attract, supported

5621
04:28:39.525 --> 04:28:41.645
and rehome disappears, the people

5622
04:28:41.645 --> 04:28:43.245
with the knowledge and experience are gone.

5623
04:28:44.035 --> 04:28:46.525
That does not protect greyhounds, that puts 'em at risk.

5624
04:28:46.995 --> 04:28:49.165
This industry is not perfect, but it is improving

5625
04:28:49.275 --> 04:28:51.165
because of regulation transparency

5626
04:28:51.225 --> 04:28:53.125
and people who have adapted again

5627
04:28:53.125 --> 04:28:54.765
and again to meet higher standards.

5628
04:28:55.505 --> 04:28:57.485
I'm proud of what I have achieved, proud

5629
04:28:57.485 --> 04:28:58.565
of the greyhounds we have raised

5630
04:28:58.705 --> 04:28:59.885
and proud of the greyhounds.

5631
04:28:59.885 --> 04:29:02.445
We have helped. If this bill is to proceed,

5632
04:29:02.515 --> 04:29:04.965
must include a five year stage wind down period

5633
04:29:05.305 --> 04:29:07.245
and fair compensation over people's assets

5634
04:29:07.705 --> 04:29:10.845
so businesses can close responsibly, staff can be supported,

5635
04:29:11.185 --> 04:29:13.405
and families have a realistic opportunity

5636
04:29:13.425 --> 04:29:14.925
to find alternative income.

5637
04:29:15.705 --> 04:29:17.045
I'm asking you respectfully

5638
04:29:17.065 --> 04:29:19.245
and sincerely not to erase an industry

5639
04:29:19.515 --> 04:29:21.925
that is doing the work, not to punish families

5640
04:29:21.925 --> 04:29:23.405
who have done everything required of them,

5641
04:29:23.905 --> 04:29:26.245
and not to dismantle a system that protects thousands

5642
04:29:26.245 --> 04:29:27.325
of greyhounds across New Zealand.

5643
04:29:28.345 --> 04:29:29.725
Let us continue improving.

5644
04:29:29.985 --> 04:29:31.085
Let us continue caring

5645
04:29:31.305 --> 04:29:32.845
and let us continue doing the work

5646
04:29:32.845 --> 04:29:34.525
that actually protects the greyhounds.

5647
04:29:34.975 --> 04:29:35.975
Thank you for listening.

5648
04:29:36.975 --> 04:29:39.805
Thank you very much. Are there any questions, members?

5649
04:29:42.975 --> 04:29:45.355
No. Thank you. And thank you for sharing your story.

5650
04:29:45.385 --> 04:29:47.555
It's a, it's really important for us to hear the social

5651
04:29:47.655 --> 04:29:50.195
and the, um, the real family side of it too.

5652
04:29:50.295 --> 04:29:51.275
So thank you very much for that.

5653
04:29:56.095 --> 04:29:58.795
Um, right, we have Emma

5654
04:29:59.415 --> 04:30:00.565
Reddy ready

5655
04:30:03.595 --> 04:30:06.655
online. Hi Emma.

5656
04:30:07.475 --> 04:30:09.575
Hi, how are you? Very well, thank you.

5657
04:30:09.715 --> 04:30:10.715
You have 10 minutes.

5658
04:30:11.775 --> 04:30:13.895
Excellent. So my name is Emma Reddy.

5659
04:30:13.915 --> 04:30:15.975
I'm currently the on track veterinarian at

5660
04:30:15.975 --> 04:30:17.015
the Christchurch Greyhound.

5661
04:30:17.475 --> 04:30:19.015
That's, we are about a third

5662
04:30:19.075 --> 04:30:20.815
of all Greyhound racing has taken place.

5663
04:30:21.645 --> 04:30:23.015
I've worked there for four years.

5664
04:30:23.105 --> 04:30:25.695
Prior to that, I was a regulatory veterinarian at NPI,

5665
04:30:26.195 --> 04:30:28.735
but most of my career was as an equine vet in Christchurch.

5666
04:30:29.675 --> 04:30:32.335
As far as I'm aware, I'm the only race day vet

5667
04:30:32.405 --> 04:30:33.575
that covers greyhounds,

5668
04:30:33.575 --> 04:30:35.255
but can cover both horse codes as well.

5669
04:30:37.195 --> 04:30:39.085
When people have asked me what I do for a living,

5670
04:30:39.485 --> 04:30:42.205
I tell them my job and then I quickly follow up

5671
04:30:42.205 --> 04:30:44.525
with a description to overcome their preconceptions.

5672
04:30:45.365 --> 04:30:47.605
I describe that I check every dog at the races

5673
04:30:48.305 --> 04:30:49.445
and then recheck something

5674
04:30:49.445 --> 04:30:51.765
after they race, mostly only as a precaution.

5675
04:30:52.725 --> 04:30:55.565
I tell them I'm in a privileged position that all the costs

5676
04:30:55.565 --> 04:30:58.645
of the medical, all the dog's medical needs are paid for

5677
04:30:58.665 --> 04:31:00.045
by Greyhound racing New Zealand

5678
04:31:00.985 --> 04:31:04.085
and that the dog's long-term welfare is my only priority.

5679
04:31:05.005 --> 04:31:07.045
I also say that the dogs are treated

5680
04:31:07.065 --> 04:31:08.525
by specialist veterinary surgeons.

5681
04:31:08.545 --> 04:31:10.765
Animal orthopedics have access

5682
04:31:10.765 --> 04:31:13.365
to rehabilitation aids like physios and water walkers,

5683
04:31:14.385 --> 04:31:16.325
and that the dogs are carefully re-homed

5684
04:31:16.505 --> 04:31:18.005
and their medical needs related

5685
04:31:18.025 --> 04:31:20.005
to the injury are paid for, for the rest of their lives.

5686
04:31:21.535 --> 04:31:23.085
After this conversation, I find

5687
04:31:23.085 --> 04:31:24.525
that people appear a bit more at ease.

5688
04:31:24.955 --> 04:31:26.885
They become comfortable with the job, the sport,

5689
04:31:27.065 --> 04:31:28.245
and they're often really keen

5690
04:31:28.245 --> 04:31:30.045
to ask me some questions and discuss it.

5691
04:31:31.865 --> 04:31:34.055
Every Greyhound race day is highly regulated,

5692
04:31:34.185 --> 04:31:37.095
their systems in place so that any welfare concerns

5693
04:31:37.095 --> 04:31:38.695
that I have can be heard and addressed.

5694
04:31:39.485 --> 04:31:42.295
Just last week I was on an ad hoc committee ensuring

5695
04:31:42.295 --> 04:31:43.295
that the track was safe.

5696
04:31:43.295 --> 04:31:46.295
After a We Weather event, I often see new

5697
04:31:46.295 --> 04:31:47.935
and updated policies and rule changes.

5698
04:31:48.295 --> 04:31:51.775
I have a chance to add to them all in an effort

5699
04:31:51.775 --> 04:31:52.815
to keep improving welfare.

5700
04:31:54.645 --> 04:31:57.125
I also have the oversight to stand down docks.

5701
04:31:57.715 --> 04:32:00.525
This means preventing them from racing for a number of days,

5702
04:32:00.525 --> 04:32:01.565
which is of my choosing.

5703
04:32:02.765 --> 04:32:04.205
I do this if I find an injury,

5704
04:32:04.425 --> 04:32:06.885
but I also do it if I notice any clinical finding

5705
04:32:07.185 --> 04:32:08.925
that's indicating a potential injury.

5706
04:32:09.425 --> 04:32:11.285
So I can do it just precautionary.

5707
04:32:13.795 --> 04:32:15.935
It is difficult to compare this level of oversight

5708
04:32:15.955 --> 04:32:18.895
to working at a horse race meeting at the horses.

5709
04:32:19.035 --> 04:32:20.735
The interaction with the stewards is limited.

5710
04:32:21.365 --> 04:32:23.975
There's less involvement in policies concerning welfares.

5711
04:32:23.975 --> 04:32:27.055
At my level, the checks on horses are nearly always

5712
04:32:27.125 --> 04:32:29.175
post-race and only if requested.

5713
04:32:30.905 --> 04:32:32.415
There is nothing comparable

5714
04:32:32.635 --> 04:32:34.495
to the Greyhound Racing New Zealand program

5715
04:32:34.715 --> 04:32:36.175
for injuries and rehabilitation.

5716
04:32:37.275 --> 04:32:40.895
And at the horses economics is a major factor in deciding

5717
04:32:40.915 --> 04:32:42.495
the future of an injured racehorse.

5718
04:32:44.125 --> 04:32:46.095
It's also really difficult to compare the results,

5719
04:32:46.095 --> 04:32:48.295
the veterinary exams post race between horses and dogs.

5720
04:32:49.555 --> 04:32:51.055
If I was in clinical practice

5721
04:32:51.055 --> 04:32:52.695
and I wanted to examine a horse for an

5722
04:32:52.755 --> 04:32:54.855
or a lameness, I'd always go there

5723
04:32:54.855 --> 04:32:56.895
before it worked, even if it was only jogging

5724
04:32:57.305 --> 04:32:58.525
and if it had already jogged,

5725
04:32:58.545 --> 04:33:00.685
I'd come back in the afternoon at least four hours

5726
04:33:00.685 --> 04:33:01.725
later, if not longer.

5727
04:33:03.935 --> 04:33:06.635
The horses are prey animals. They're being enticed to run.

5728
04:33:06.865 --> 04:33:08.235
They have a high adrenaline

5729
04:33:08.255 --> 04:33:09.915
and they're innately wanting to disguise an

5730
04:33:09.915 --> 04:33:11.555
injury for horses.

5731
04:33:11.735 --> 04:33:14.675
We compare serial heart rates over time to indicate issues.

5732
04:33:15.935 --> 04:33:16.975
It's very non-specific.

5733
04:33:17.525 --> 04:33:19.975
Serious injuries are able to be found post-race,

5734
04:33:20.195 --> 04:33:21.535
but it's common for injuries

5735
04:33:21.555 --> 04:33:23.255
to be not found until the next day.

5736
04:33:24.305 --> 04:33:26.495
Greyhounds and predators that are born to chase,

5737
04:33:27.045 --> 04:33:30.015
there's even rules preventing them from racing if they show

5738
04:33:30.015 --> 04:33:31.855
any deviation from chasing the lure

5739
04:33:31.855 --> 04:33:32.935
for the duration of the race.

5740
04:33:33.755 --> 04:33:35.855
The dogs are smaller, they're well-defined.

5741
04:33:36.075 --> 04:33:38.775
It makes palpation really easy to find injuries.

5742
04:33:39.845 --> 04:33:41.495
Most injuries are able to be found

5743
04:33:41.675 --> 04:33:43.335
as we have a compulsory call down period

5744
04:33:43.335 --> 04:33:44.375
of at least 15 minutes

5745
04:33:44.375 --> 04:33:46.055
after they race, before they're examined.

5746
04:33:47.675 --> 04:33:49.245
It's hard to understand how it was decided

5747
04:33:49.245 --> 04:33:51.365
that there's too many injuries and greyhound racing.

5748
04:33:52.155 --> 04:33:53.285
Comparing the stats

5749
04:33:53.285 --> 04:33:54.565
to the other horse codes is like

5750
04:33:54.565 --> 04:33:55.725
comparing apples and oranges.

5751
04:33:57.055 --> 04:33:59.475
If the decision was made just comparing fatalities,

5752
04:33:59.745 --> 04:34:01.955
then the rate in greyhound racing is about half

5753
04:34:01.955 --> 04:34:02.995
that of thoroughbred racing.

5754
04:34:03.335 --> 04:34:05.155
As far, as far as last year,

5755
04:34:08.245 --> 04:34:09.535
what I wanna know is who decided

5756
04:34:09.535 --> 04:34:10.775
that New Zealand Greyhound racing

5757
04:34:11.035 --> 04:34:12.335
injury rate is the problem.

5758
04:34:12.715 --> 04:34:14.375
But the Australian injury rate,

5759
04:34:14.385 --> 04:34:16.215
which is a little higher, is okay.

5760
04:34:16.685 --> 04:34:17.855
This seems to be the case

5761
04:34:17.915 --> 04:34:19.695
as the government has included in the bill

5762
04:34:19.715 --> 04:34:21.975
to bring in thousands of races from Australia.

5763
04:34:24.275 --> 04:34:26.955
I do strongly oppose the bill in its current form.

5764
04:34:26.975 --> 04:34:29.675
It specifically allows for dog racing for recreation

5765
04:34:30.055 --> 04:34:32.635
and betting if it's in, if it's Australian.

5766
04:34:32.855 --> 04:34:35.275
And it just seems solely aimed at taking the livelihood

5767
04:34:35.275 --> 04:34:36.275
of the current participants.

5768
04:34:37.295 --> 04:34:38.595
If the bill proceeded,

5769
04:34:38.875 --> 04:34:40.835
I would recommend extending the shutdown date.

5770
04:34:41.225 --> 04:34:43.635
This is in line with the recommendation from New Zealand

5771
04:34:43.635 --> 04:34:46.435
Veterinary Association physician statement from 2024.

5772
04:34:47.345 --> 04:34:50.035
This statement recommended a slow in measured shutdown

5773
04:34:50.205 --> 04:34:53.235
preventing swamping of rehoming with large numbers

5774
04:34:53.255 --> 04:34:54.275
of dogs all at once.

5775
04:34:55.425 --> 04:34:57.155
This new date, a new, sorry,

5776
04:34:57.315 --> 04:35:00.115
a new date would also be more in line with Tasmania's plans

5777
04:35:02.085 --> 04:35:05.255
betting turnover from Australian gr Greyhound racing over

5778
04:35:05.255 --> 04:35:06.935
this extended time can be accumulated

5779
04:35:07.155 --> 04:35:09.015
to make a long-term plan of how

5780
04:35:09.015 --> 04:35:11.335
to manage all re-homed greyhounds for their lifetime.

5781
04:35:11.725 --> 04:35:13.495
That would then match the level of care

5782
04:35:13.495 --> 04:35:15.295
and diligence that's currently offered as part

5783
04:35:15.295 --> 04:35:18.055
of the Greyhound racing New Zealand's re-homing system

5784
04:35:18.055 --> 04:35:21.235
that I've seen every day,

5785
04:35:21.325 --> 04:35:23.915
every race I see the handlers, they pat their dogs,

5786
04:35:24.025 --> 04:35:25.755
they give them cuddles and kisses on the head.

5787
04:35:25.945 --> 04:35:28.155
They even the gruff trainers rub their ears

5788
04:35:28.155 --> 04:35:29.675
and give them a little pat under the chin.

5789
04:35:30.935 --> 04:35:32.555
New Zealand on a whole agrees

5790
04:35:32.555 --> 04:35:34.075
that animals are okay in industry.

5791
04:35:34.255 --> 04:35:36.115
We have heaps of different species being farmed.

5792
04:35:36.135 --> 04:35:37.395
We have commercial fishery.

5793
04:35:38.015 --> 04:35:41.075
New Zealand also agrees of using animals for entertainment.

5794
04:35:41.255 --> 04:35:43.635
We have horse racing, we have dog breeding everywhere.

5795
04:35:43.925 --> 04:35:45.115
Shows have pony rides

5796
04:35:45.115 --> 04:35:48.075
and Jack Russell racing hunting is gaining in popularity.

5797
04:35:49.115 --> 04:35:51.475
I think that if the public was informed of the level

5798
04:35:51.495 --> 04:35:53.795
of regulation, the veterinary involvement

5799
04:35:53.795 --> 04:35:56.205
and the investment that I see see in welfare at the,

5800
04:35:56.225 --> 04:35:57.405
at a Greyhound race meeting.

5801
04:35:57.905 --> 04:36:00.165
And then they were asked if the participants deserve

