rates per number of starts.

6450
05:05:16.115 --> 05:05:17.415
But for the dogs involved,

6451
05:05:17.805 --> 05:05:20.215
that context does not make broken bones

6452
05:05:20.315 --> 05:05:22.295
or sudden heart failure any less real.

6453
05:05:23.105 --> 05:05:26.635
Even a low percentage still translates into hundreds

6454
05:05:26.795 --> 05:05:28.915
of individual animals harmed each year.

6455
05:05:29.535 --> 05:05:32.675
And it's a model that fails to account for cumulative risk.

6456
05:05:34.245 --> 05:05:36.805
We are also told that the industry has made improvements

6457
05:05:37.345 --> 05:05:40.685
and safe acknowledges that some changes have been made such

6458
05:05:40.685 --> 05:05:42.285
as better euthanasia controls.

6459
05:05:43.265 --> 05:05:45.885
But the question before this committee today is not whether

6460
05:05:45.885 --> 05:05:47.445
there have been reforms on paper,

6461
05:05:47.945 --> 05:05:50.365
but whether dogs are being protected in practice.

6462
05:05:51.105 --> 05:05:53.165
And the evidence shows they are not.

6463
05:05:55.225 --> 05:05:57.545
Multiple reviews, as you know, over more than a decade,

6464
05:05:57.745 --> 05:05:59.425
examined this industry in depth.

6465
05:06:00.095 --> 05:06:02.305
Each found recurring welfare failures,

6466
05:06:02.815 --> 05:06:05.865
each prompted new rules and oversight mechanisms,

6467
05:06:06.525 --> 05:06:07.705
and dogs continue

6468
05:06:07.705 --> 05:06:10.225
to suffer catastrophic injuries and sudden deaths.

6469
05:06:11.555 --> 05:06:15.125
What those reviews, alter reviews ultimately show is

6470
05:06:15.125 --> 05:06:17.685
that this is not a problem of one bad track

6471
05:06:18.065 --> 05:06:21.085
or one rogue trainer or one unlucky race.

6472
05:06:21.875 --> 05:06:23.885
It's a problem of the activity itself.

6473
05:06:25.475 --> 05:06:27.825
Commercial greyhound racing requires dogs

6474
05:06:27.825 --> 05:06:31.305
to sprint at extreme speeds in close quarters under

6475
05:06:31.505 --> 05:06:34.465
competitive pressure for the purposes of gambling

6476
05:06:34.795 --> 05:06:37.105
where they are regarded as financial assets.

6477
05:06:37.975 --> 05:06:40.585
That combination carries unavoidable risks

6478
05:06:40.935 --> 05:06:43.705
that regulation has not and cannot remove.

6479
05:06:45.335 --> 05:06:47.995
We are also told that people in the industry care deeply

6480
05:06:47.995 --> 05:06:49.715
about their dogs and

6481
05:06:49.715 --> 05:06:51.795
that their livelihoods depend on racing.

6482
05:06:52.775 --> 05:06:56.155
And safe does not dispute that many individuals form bonds

6483
05:06:56.155 --> 05:06:58.235
with these animals and care about these dogs

6484
05:06:58.775 --> 05:07:01.395
and that families rely on this industry for income.

6485
05:07:02.385 --> 05:07:06.485
But caring about these dogs is not the same as being able

6486
05:07:06.485 --> 05:07:09.405
to protect them from harm within a commercial racing system.

6487
05:07:10.075 --> 05:07:13.205
When the evidence shows that the harm remains endemic

6488
05:07:14.145 --> 05:07:17.805
and economic reliance cannot justify continuing an activity

6489
05:07:18.155 --> 05:07:20.085
that foreseeably injures animals

6490
05:07:20.585 --> 05:07:23.765
and falls short of the standards parliament has set within

6491
05:07:23.865 --> 05:07:25.085
our animal welfare laws.

6492
05:07:26.575 --> 05:07:29.825
This bill is not a judgment on individual character.

6493
05:07:30.285 --> 05:07:33.345
It is a judgment about whether a particular industry model

6494
05:07:33.565 --> 05:07:35.905
can meet modern animal welfare standards

6495
05:07:36.605 --> 05:07:38.265
and the evidence shows that it cannot.

6496
05:07:40.205 --> 05:07:42.065
Um, before I close, I wanna quickly note

6497
